casebody.data:
State of Connecticut v. Edward M. Keelan (10891)

Laveky, Landau and Heiman, Js.

Argued January 8 — decision released February 2, 1993 Edward Keelan, pro se, the appellant (defendant). James A. Kitten, assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, was Mary M. Galvin, state’s attorney, and Frank McQuade, supervisory assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
